Sure, here is how you can define the struct and the `show` method in Go:

```go
type FloatWithUnits struct {
    value float64
    unit  string
}

func (fwu FloatWithUnits) show() string {
    return fmt.Sprintf("%f %s", fwu.value, fwu.unit)
}
```

The `show` method uses the `fmt.Sprintf` function to format the `value` and `unit` fields as a string, with a space between them.
